Package: FocusGroup
Type: Package
Title: Focus Group Simulation Using LLM Agents
Version: 0.5.1
Authors@R:
    person("Ali", "Sanaei", , "sanaei@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Researchers can simulate moderated focus group discussions in which
    large language model (LLM) agents speak from supplied personas. Personas may
    be written directly or assembled from demographic records, with survey
    responses added when available. Configurable turn-taking rules govern
    participant selection, while phased scripts guide moderator prompts and
    participant exchanges. The resulting transcripts are intended for piloting
    moderator guides and discussion protocols rather than estimating human
    attitudes. Transcript tools examine participation and conversational patterns
    through descriptive statistics and optional text analysis. The simulation and
    its model-dependent analyses call configured providers through the 'LLMR'
    package. An optional 'Shiny' interface runs sessions and examines saved
    transcripts.
